  "prompt": "Is OBC quota applicable to those who sold their property?",
  "response": "The applicability of OBC (Other Backward Class) quota to someone who has sold their property depends on various factors:\n\n1. General Criteria:\n- Selling property does not automatically disqualify a person from OBC benefits\n- OBC status is primarily based on caste/community, not property ownership\n\n2. Income Criteria:\n- If property sale significantly increases income beyond prescribed limits\n- Income threshold may affect OBC quota eligibility\n\n3. Specific Considerations:\n- Creamy Layer status\n- Total family income after property sale\n- Purpose of property sale\n\n4. Recommendation:\n- Consult local OBC certification authority\n- Verify specific state-wise guidelines\n- Get updated information from relevant government department\n\n5. Documentation:\n- May need to provide:\n- Income certificate\n- Caste certificate\n- Property sale details\n\nImportant Note: OBC quota rules can vary between states and central/state institutions, so local specific regulations should be carefully checked.\n\nIt's best to directly consult local authorities or get official verification for precise information regarding your specific situation.",
